<div1 type="letter">

<pb facs="nei.j4c.64.28" />

<fw type="curatorial">28</fw>

<opener>
<dateline>
5835 Vine Street<lb/>
Lincoln, Nebraska 68505<lb/>
November 16, 1972
</dateline>

<address>
<addrLine>Mr. Howard Lyon</addrLine>
<addrLine>722 E. Marlette Avenue</addrLine>
<addrLine>Phoenix, Arizona 85014</addrLine>
</address>

<salute>Dear Howard Lyon:</salute>
</opener>
<p>Many thanks for that most generous letter.</p>

<p>It is good news that you may be in this part of the country for Neihardt Day in August. We would all be glad to see you, certainly, for we remember your visit with pleasure.</p>

<p>We keep very busy here with correspondence and other matters related to my work. I am busy with the second volume of my autobiography.</p>
<closer>
<salute>With all kind thoughts, your friend,</salute>



<signed>John G. Neihardt</signed>


<note>JGN:nh</note>
</closer>

</div1>
